{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to talk about the transformed media landscape,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and what it means for anybody who has a message that they want to get out"},{"time":8000,"text":"to anywhere in the world."},{"time":10000,"text":"And I want to illustrate that by telling a couple of stories"},{"time":12000,"text":"about that transformation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14000,"text":"I'll start here. Last November there was a presidential election."},{"time":17000,"text":"You probably read something about it in the papers."},{"time":20000,"text":"And there was some concern that in some parts of the country"},{"time":23000,"text":"there might be voter suppression."},{"time":25000,"text":"And so a plan came up to video the vote."},{"time":27000,"text":"And the idea was that individual citizens"},{"time":30000,"text":"with phones capable of taking photos or making video"},{"time":33000,"text":"would document their polling places,"},{"time":35000,"text":"on the lookout for any kind of voter suppression techniques,"},{"time":38000,"text":"and would upload this to a central place."},{"time":40000,"text":"And that this would operate as a kind of citizen observation --"},{"time":44000,"text":"that citizens would not be there just to cast individual votes,"},{"time":48000,"text":"but also to help ensure the sanctity of the vote overall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52000,"text":"So this is a pattern that assumes we're all in this together."},{"time":56000,"text":"What matters here"},{"time":58000,"text":"isn't technical capital,"},{"time":60000,"text":"it's social capital."},{"time":62000,"text":"These tools don't get socially interesting"},{"time":65000,"text":"until they get technologically boring."},{"time":68000,"text":"It isn't when the shiny new tools show up"},{"time":72000,"text":"that their uses start permeating society."},{"time":74000,"text":"It's when everybody is able to take them for granted."},{"time":78000,"text":"Because now that media is increasingly social,"},{"time":81000,"text":"innovation can happen anywhere"},{"time":84000,"text":"that people can take for granted the idea that we're all in this together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"And so we're starting to see a media landscape"},{"time":91000,"text":"in which innovation is happening everywhere,"},{"time":94000,"text":"and moving from one spot to another."},{"time":96000,"text":"That is a huge transformation."},{"time":100000,"text":"Not to put too fine a point on it, the moment we're living through --"},{"time":103000,"text":"the moment our historical generation is living through --"},{"time":106000,"text":"is the largest increase in expressive capability"},{"time":110000,"text":"in human history."},{"time":112000,"text":"Now that's a big claim. I'm going to try to back it up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114000,"text":"There are only four periods in the last 500 years"},{"time":118000,"text":"where media has changed enough to qualify for the label \"revolution.\""},{"time":121000,"text":"The first one is the famous one, the printing press:"},{"time":124000,"text":"movable type, oil-based inks, that whole complex of innovations"},{"time":127000,"text":"that made printing possible"},{"time":129000,"text":"and turned Europe upside-down, starting in the middle of the 1400s."},{"time":132000,"text":"Then, a couple of hundred years ago,"},{"time":134000,"text":"there was innovation in two-way communication,"},{"time":136000,"text":"conversational media: first the telegraph, then the telephone."},{"time":139000,"text":"Slow, text-based conversations,"},{"time":142000,"text":"then real-time voice based conversations."},{"time":144000,"text":"Then, about 150 years ago,"},{"time":146000,"text":"there was a revolution in recorded media other than print:"},{"time":149000,"text":"first photos, then recorded sound,"},{"time":152000,"text":"then movies, all encoded onto physical objects."},{"time":155000,"text":"And finally, about 100 years ago, the harnessing of electromagnetic spectrum"},{"time":158000,"text":"to send sound and images through the air -- radio and television."},{"time":162000,"text":"This is the media landscape as we knew it in the 20th century."},{"time":166000,"text":"This is what those of us of a certain age"},{"time":169000,"text":"grew up with, and are used to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172000,"text":"But there is a curious asymmetry here."},{"time":174000,"text":"The media that is good at creating conversations"},{"time":177000,"text":"is no good at creating groups."},{"time":179000,"text":"And the media that's good at creating groups"},{"time":181000,"text":"is no good at creating conversations."},{"time":183000,"text":"If you want to have a conversation"},{"time":185000,"text":"in this world, you have it with one other person."},{"time":187000,"text":"If you want to address a group, you get the same message"},{"time":190000,"text":"and you give it to everybody in the group,"},{"time":192000,"text":"whether you're doing that with a broadcasting tower or a printing press."},{"time":196000,"text":"That was the media landscape"},{"time":198000,"text":"as we had it in the twentieth century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"And this is what changed."},{"time":202000,"text":"This thing that looks like a peacock hit a windscreen"},{"time":204000,"text":"is Bill Cheswick's map of the Internet."},{"time":206000,"text":"He traces the edges of the individual networks"},{"time":208000,"text":"and then color codes them."},{"time":210000,"text":"The Internet is the first medium in history"},{"time":212000,"text":"that has native support for groups"},{"time":214000,"text":"and conversation at the same time."},{"time":217000,"text":"Whereas the phone gave us the one-to-one pattern,"},{"time":220000,"text":"and television, radio, magazines, books,"},{"time":222000,"text":"gave us the one-to-many pattern,"},{"time":224000,"text":"the Internet gives us the many-to-many pattern."},{"time":226000,"text":"For the first time,"},{"time":228000,"text":"media is natively good at supporting these kinds of conversations."},{"time":232000,"text":"That's one of the big changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"The second big change"},{"time":237000,"text":"is that, as all media gets digitized,"},{"time":239000,"text":"the Internet also becomes the mode of carriage"},{"time":242000,"text":"for all other media,"},{"time":244000,"text":"meaning that phone calls migrate to the Internet,"},{"time":246000,"text":"magazines migrate to the Internet, movies migrate to the Internet."},{"time":249000,"text":"And that means that every medium"},{"time":251000,"text":"is right next door to every other medium."},{"time":256000,"text":"Put another way,"},{"time":259000,"text":"media is increasingly less just a source of information,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and it is increasingly more a site of coordination,"},{"time":265000,"text":"because groups that see or hear or watch or listen to something"},{"time":268000,"text":"can now gather around and talk to each other as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"And the third big change"},{"time":275000,"text":"is that members of the former audience, as Dan Gilmore calls them,"},{"time":277000,"text":"can now also be producers and not consumers."},{"time":281000,"text":"Every time a new consumer"},{"time":283000,"text":"joins this media landscape"},{"time":285000,"text":"a new producer joins as well,"},{"time":287000,"text":"because the same equipment --"},{"time":289000,"text":"phones, computers --"},{"time":291000,"text":"let you consume and produce."},{"time":293000,"text":"It's as if, when you bought a book, they threw in the printing press for free;"},{"time":296000,"text":"it's like you had a phone that could turn into a radio"},{"time":298000,"text":"if you pressed the right buttons."},{"time":300000,"text":"That is a huge change"},{"time":303000,"text":"in the media landscape we're used to."},{"time":305000,"text":"And it's not just Internet or no Internet."},{"time":308000,"text":"We've had the Internet in its public form"},{"time":310000,"text":"for almost 20 years now,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and it's still changing"},{"time":314000,"text":"as the media becomes more social."},{"time":316000,"text":"It's still changing patterns"},{"time":318000,"text":"even among groups who know how to deal with the Internet well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"Second story."},{"time":323000,"text":"Last May, China in the Sichuan province"},{"time":325000,"text":"had a terrible earthquake, 7.9 magnitude,"},{"time":328000,"text":"massive destruction in a wide area, as the Richter Scale has it."},{"time":332000,"text":"And the earthquake was reported as it was happening."},{"time":338000,"text":"People were texting from their phones. They were taking photos of buildings."},{"time":341000,"text":"They were taking videos of buildings shaking."},{"time":344000,"text":"They were uploading it to QQ, China's largest Internet service."},{"time":347000,"text":"They were Twittering it."},{"time":349000,"text":"And so as the quake was happening"},{"time":352000,"text":"the news was reported."},{"time":354000,"text":"And because of the social connections,"},{"time":356000,"text":"Chinese students coming elsewhere, and going to school,"},{"time":359000,"text":"or businesses in the rest of the world opening offices in China --"},{"time":363000,"text":"there were people listening all over the world, hearing this news."},{"time":367000,"text":"The BBC got their first wind of the Chinese quake from Twitter."},{"time":372000,"text":"Twitter announced the existence of the quake"},{"time":375000,"text":"several minutes before the US Geological Survey"},{"time":377000,"text":"had anything up online for anybody to read."},{"time":381000,"text":"The last time China had a quake of that magnitude"},{"time":384000,"text":"it took them three months to admit that it had happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"Now they might have liked to have done that here,"},{"time":392000,"text":"rather than seeing these pictures go up online."},{"time":395000,"text":"But they weren't given that choice,"},{"time":398000,"text":"because their own citizens beat them to the punch."},{"time":401000,"text":"Even the government learned of the earthquake from their own citizens,"},{"time":405000,"text":"rather than from the Xinhua News Agency."},{"time":408000,"text":"And this stuff rippled like wildfire."},{"time":410000,"text":"For a while there"},{"time":412000,"text":"the top 10 most clicked links on Twitter,"},{"time":414000,"text":"the global short messaging service --"},{"time":416000,"text":"nine of the top 10 links were about the quake."},{"time":419000,"text":"People collating information,"},{"time":421000,"text":"pointing people to news sources,"},{"time":423000,"text":"pointing people to the US geological survey."},{"time":425000,"text":"The 10th one was kittens on a treadmill, but that's the Internet for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":430000,"text":"But nine of the 10 in those first hours."},{"time":433000,"text":"And within half a day donation sites were up,"},{"time":437000,"text":"and donations were pouring in from all around the world."},{"time":441000,"text":"This was an incredible, coordinated global response."},{"time":445000,"text":"And the Chinese then, in one of their periods of media openness,"},{"time":447000,"text":"decided that they were going to let it go,"},{"time":449000,"text":"that they were going to let this citizen reporting fly."},{"time":454000,"text":"And then this happened."},{"time":456000,"text":"People began to figure out, in the Sichuan Provence,"},{"time":458000,"text":"that the reason so many school buildings had collapsed --"},{"time":461000,"text":"because tragically the earthquake happened during a school day --"},{"time":465000,"text":"the reason so many school buildings collapsed"},{"time":467000,"text":"is that corrupt officials had taken bribes"},{"time":469000,"text":"to allow those building to be built to less than code."},{"time":473000,"text":"And so they started, the citizen journalists started"}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"reporting that as well. And there was an incredible picture."},{"time":479000,"text":"You may have seen in on the front page of the New York Times."},{"time":481000,"text":"A local official literally prostrated himself in the street,"},{"time":485000,"text":"in front of these protesters,"},{"time":487000,"text":"in order to get them to go away."},{"time":490000,"text":"Essentially to say, \"We will do anything to placate you,"},{"time":492000,"text":"just please stop protesting in public.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":495000,"text":"But these are people who have been radicalized,"},{"time":497000,"text":"because, thanks to the one child policy,"},{"time":499000,"text":"they have lost everyone in their next generation."},{"time":502000,"text":"Someone who has seen the death of a single child"},{"time":504000,"text":"now has nothing to lose."},{"time":506000,"text":"And so the protest kept going."},{"time":508000,"text":"And finally the Chinese cracked down."},{"time":511000,"text":"That was enough of citizen media."},{"time":514000,"text":"And so they began to arrest the protesters."},{"time":516000,"text":"They began to shut down the media that the protests were happening on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"China is probably the most successful"},{"time":524000,"text":"manager of Internet censorship in the world,"},{"time":527000,"text":"using something that is widely described as the Great Firewall of China."},{"time":531000,"text":"And the Great Firewall of China"},{"time":533000,"text":"is a set of observation points"},{"time":535000,"text":"that assume that media is produced by professionals,"},{"time":539000,"text":"it mostly comes in from the outside world,"},{"time":542000,"text":"it comes in relatively sparse chunks,"},{"time":545000,"text":"and it comes in relatively slowly."},{"time":548000,"text":"And because of those four characteristics"},{"time":550000,"text":"they are able to filter it as it comes into the country."},{"time":554000,"text":"But like the Maginot Line,"},{"time":556000,"text":"the great firewall of China was facing in the wrong direction"},{"time":559000,"text":"for this challenge,"},{"time":561000,"text":"because not one of those four things was true in this environment."},{"time":567000,"text":"The media was produced locally. It was produced by amateurs."},{"time":569000,"text":"It was produced quickly. And it was produced at such an incredible abundance"},{"time":574000,"text":"that there was no way to filter it as it appeared."},{"time":578000,"text":"And so now the Chinese government, who for a dozen years,"},{"time":581000,"text":"has quite successfully filtered the web,"},{"time":585000,"text":"is now in the position of having to decide"},{"time":587000,"text":"whether to allow or shut down entire services,"},{"time":591000,"text":"because the transformation to amateur media"},{"time":594000,"text":"is so enormous that they can't deal with it any other way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598000,"text":"And in fact that is happening this week."},{"time":600000,"text":"On the 20th anniversary of Tiananmen"},{"time":602000,"text":"they just, two days ago, announced"},{"time":605000,"text":"that they were simply shutting down access to Twitter,"},{"time":608000,"text":"because there was no way to filter it other than that."},{"time":612000,"text":"They had to turn the spigot entirely off."},{"time":616000,"text":"Now these changes don't just affect people who want to censor messages."},{"time":620000,"text":"They also affect people who want to send messages,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"because this is really a transformation of the ecosystem as a whole,"},{"time":626000,"text":"not just a particular strategy."},{"time":628000,"text":"The classic media problem, from the 20th century"},{"time":632000,"text":"is, how does an organization have a message"},{"time":634000,"text":"that they want to get out"},{"time":636000,"text":"to a group of people distributed at the edges of a network."},{"time":638000,"text":"And here is the twentieth century answer."},{"time":641000,"text":"Bundle up the message. Send the same message to everybody."},{"time":645000,"text":"National message. Targeted individuals."},{"time":647000,"text":"Relatively sparse number of producers."},{"time":649000,"text":"Very expensive to do,"},{"time":651000,"text":"so there is not a lot of competition."},{"time":653000,"text":"This is how you reach people."},{"time":655000,"text":"All of that is over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658000,"text":"We are increasingly in a landscape where media is global,"},{"time":661000,"text":"social, ubiquitous and cheap."},{"time":664000,"text":"Now most organizations that are trying to send messages"},{"time":669000,"text":"to the outside world, to the distributed collection of the audience,"},{"time":673000,"text":"are now used to this change."},{"time":675000,"text":"The audience can talk back."},{"time":677000,"text":"And that's a little freaky. But you can get used to it after a while, as people do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682000,"text":"But that's not the really crazy change that we're living in the middle of."},{"time":686000,"text":"The really crazy change is here:"},{"time":689000,"text":"it's the fact that they are no longer disconnected from each other,"},{"time":693000,"text":"the fact that former consumers are now producers,"},{"time":696000,"text":"the fact that the audience can talk directly to one another;"},{"time":699000,"text":"because there is a lot more amateurs than professionals,"},{"time":702000,"text":"and because the size of the network,"},{"time":705000,"text":"the complexity of the network is actually the square"},{"time":708000,"text":"of the number of participants,"},{"time":710000,"text":"meaning that the network, when it grows large,"},{"time":712000,"text":"grows very, very large."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714000,"text":"As recently at last decade,"},{"time":716000,"text":"most of the media that was available for public consumption"},{"time":719000,"text":"was produced by professionals."},{"time":721000,"text":"Those days are over, never to return."},{"time":725000,"text":"It is the green lines now, that are the source of the free content,"},{"time":728000,"text":"which brings me to my last story."},{"time":731000,"text":"We saw some of the most imaginative use"},{"time":733000,"text":"of social media during the Obama campaign."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"And I don't mean most imaginative use in politics --"},{"time":738000,"text":"I mean most imaginative use ever."},{"time":741000,"text":"And one of the things Obama did, was they famously,"},{"time":743000,"text":"the Obama campaign did, was they famously put up"},{"time":745000,"text":"MyBarackObama.com, myBO.com"},{"time":747000,"text":"And millions of citizens rushed in to participate,"},{"time":751000,"text":"and to try and figure out how to help."},{"time":753000,"text":"An incredible conversation sprung up there."},{"time":756000,"text":"And then, this time last year,"},{"time":759000,"text":"Obama announced that he was going to change his vote on FISA,"},{"time":762000,"text":"The Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act."},{"time":764000,"text":"He had said, in January, that he would not sign a bill"},{"time":766000,"text":"that granted telecom immunity for possibly warrantless spying"},{"time":770000,"text":"on American persons."},{"time":773000,"text":"By the summer, in the middle of the general campaign,"},{"time":775000,"text":"He said, \"I've thought about the issue more. I've changed my mind."},{"time":777000,"text":"I'm going to vote for this bill.\""},{"time":779000,"text":"And many of his own supporters"},{"time":781000,"text":"on his own site went very publicly berserk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786000,"text":"It was Senator Obama when they created it. They changed the name later."},{"time":789000,"text":"\"Please get FISA right.\""},{"time":791000,"text":"Within days of this group being created"},{"time":793000,"text":"it was the fastest growing group on myBO.com;"},{"time":796000,"text":"within weeks of its being created it was the largest group."},{"time":799000,"text":"Obama had to issue a press release."},{"time":802000,"text":"He had to issue a reply."},{"time":805000,"text":"And he said essentially, \"I have considered the issue."},{"time":807000,"text":"I understand where you are coming from."},{"time":809000,"text":"But having considered it all, I'm still going to vote the way I'm going to vote."},{"time":813000,"text":"But I wanted to reach out to you and say, I understand that you disagree with me,"},{"time":816000,"text":"and I'm going to take my lumps on this one.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":819000,"text":"This didn't please anybody. But then a funny thing happened in the conversation."},{"time":823000,"text":"People in that group realized"},{"time":825000,"text":"that Obama had never shut them down."},{"time":829000,"text":"Nobody in the Obama campaign had ever tried to hide the group"},{"time":833000,"text":"or make it harder to join,"},{"time":835000,"text":"to deny its existence, to delete it,"},{"time":837000,"text":"to take to off the site."},{"time":839000,"text":"They had understood that their role"},{"time":843000,"text":"with myBO.com was to convene their supporters"},{"time":846000,"text":"but not to control their supporters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"And that is the kind of discipline"},{"time":851000,"text":"that it takes to make really mature use"},{"time":855000,"text":"of this media."},{"time":858000,"text":"Media, the media landscape that we knew,"},{"time":862000,"text":"as familiar as it was, as easy conceptually as it was"},{"time":865000,"text":"to deal with the idea that professionals broadcast"},{"time":867000,"text":"messages to amateurs,"},{"time":869000,"text":"is increasingly slipping away."},{"time":872000,"text":"In a world where media is global, social, ubiquitous and cheap,"},{"time":876000,"text":"in a world of media where the former audience"},{"time":878000,"text":"are now increasingly full participants,"},{"time":882000,"text":"in that world, media is less and less often"},{"time":886000,"text":"about crafting a single message"},{"time":889000,"text":"to be consumed by individuals."},{"time":892000,"text":"It is more and more often"},{"time":894000,"text":"a way of creating an environment for convening"},{"time":897000,"text":"and supporting groups."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899000,"text":"And the choice we face,"},{"time":901000,"text":"I mean anybody who has a message they want to have heard"},{"time":903000,"text":"anywhere in the world,"},{"time":906000,"text":"isn't whether or not that is the media environment we want to operate in."},{"time":909000,"text":"That's the media environment we've got."},{"time":911000,"text":"The question we all face now is,"},{"time":913000,"text":"\"How can we make best use of this media?"},{"time":915000,"text":"Even though it means changing the way we've always done it.\""},{"time":919000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":921000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}